✅ How to Run on Ubuntu
1️⃣ Create file
nano sigalrm.c


Paste code → Save (Ctrl+O) → Exit (Ctrl+X)

2️⃣ Compile
gcc sigalrm.c -o sigalrm

3️⃣ Run
./sigalrm

Expected Output
Parent PID: 4500
Parent waiting for SIGALRM...
Child PID: 4501 sending SIGALRM to parent...
Child sent SIGALRM to parent.

Alarm is fired! (Received SIGALRM)
Parent exiting...
